<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-399] DoM component size constraints</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-399</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello, we&apos;re wondering about the DoM component size limitations for a future DoM enabled system. The Lustre manual says the size must be aligned by 64KB:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;20.2.3.1.%C2%A0LFSlimitsforDoMcomponentsize&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;20.2.3.1.&#160;LFS limits for DoM component size&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lfs setstripe&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;allows for setting the component size for MDT layouts up to 1GB, however, the size must be also aligned by 64KB.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why is that? Another example in the documentation shows the use of 32KB, is that okay?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks much.&lt;br/&gt;
 Stephane&lt;/p&gt;</description>
